An vero rescinderent? The An here is really dis- junctive, the first alternative being involved in the preceding clause. Originally an may have been a simple interrogative, but a comparison of instances from the text of this speech will show that its characteristic use in Cicero is to introduce somewhat abrupt questions (or, then) containing a remon- strance or an ironical alternative.
